Senior Machine Learning Engineer
Mazowieckie
NR REF.: 1172355

Your new company

Bayer is a global enterprise with core competencies in the three main life sciences area of crop science, pharmaceuticals, & enabling functions. Its products and services are designed to benefit people and improve their quality of life. At Bayer you can be part of a culture where we value the passion of our employees to innovate and give them the power to change

Your new role
• Drive and lead business and innovation projects in the areas of Medical Affairs, Pharmacovigilance and Regulatory Affairs to deliver fit-for-purpose AI and data, i.e. fit-for-purpose AI and data solutions as part of digital products;
• Lead projects (technical) other ML Engineers and data scientists applying an agile approach;
• Lead scaling up activities transforming data science prototypes to end to end solutions embedded in business processes by leveraging skills across a large IT unit working with Business Domain Expert in... their daily work;
• Leads and carries out data engineering, data modeling, and AI and data infrastructure tasks;
• Leads and carries out the deployment of machine learning (ML) / deep learning (DL) models and helps improve existing ML/DL models in production;
• Design and Implement Cloud based Architectures ready to host ML models and pipelines;
• Establish strong link with stakeholders in the business to help shape and execute the digital agenda strategy;
• Create opportunities for digital product development by identifying pain points in the business to improve efficiency and decision making;
• Collaborates with scientists and analysts performing business analysis and domain modeling;
• Publish innovative methodologies, architectures and scientific discoveries in peer reviewed journals.

What you'll need to succeed
• Bachelor with long term experience, Master with long term experience or PhD with several years of industry experience in machine learning, statistics, applied mathematics or computer science, with strong knowledge of machine learning and deep learning;
• Strong track records leading the delivery of groundbreaking machine learning or data project;.
• Basic level knowledge in statistical machine learning and/or Deep Learning, in particular in Natural Language Processing, PyTorch, TensorFlow;
• Strong experience in Data Engineering (connecting to new data sources, storing the data, choose the right storage engine and transforming and cleaning the data);
• Very good knowledge of Cloud native application architecture and being able to create ML solutions in the Cloud (ideally AWS; Azure and GCP flexible of learning sth new; Infrastructure as Code);
• Very good coding knowledge in Python, familiar with at least one Cloud framework (e.g. AWS) as well as proficiency with machine learning and deep learning frameworks such as TensorFlow or PyTorch (nice to have); IaC paradigm – Terraform (or other framework, understanding the concept of IaC)
• Strong business analyst skills and strong experience interacting with very diverse customers is required (related to data engineering – understanding what’s the business purpose of collecting data and interpreting data in the right; stakeholder communication – stakeholders – medical affair, R&D, medical background, biomedical engineering, doctors, physicians, often without technical background; risk and safety management; R&D – other Data Scientists);
• Strong skills in presentation of results and outlining of solutions to the business;
• Ability to work in an interdisciplinary and agile environment;
• Fluent in English both written and spoken.

What you'll get in return
• A flexible, remote hybrid work model;
• New & exciting open office space;
• Career Development & 360° Feedback;
• Budget for Professional Development, Training, & Conferences;
• Company Bonus & Reward Structure;
• Premium Medical Care Package (including Dental & Mental health);
• Life & Travel Insurance;
• Multi-Sport Card with unlimited usage;
• Meals Subsidy in Office.

What you need to do now
If you're interested in this role, click 'apply now' to forward an up-to-date copy of your CV, or call us now.

