Sigma IT Poland is a division within NEXER GROUP – a custom software development company. In Poland, we started in 2017 and now we are 150+ crew with an office in Wrocław, Warsaw, and any day Cracow. We have the opportunity to work with world-renowned brands from Scandinavia, the UK, and Western Europe. Our goal is to grow strong, rather in competencies than in pure numbers.

If you like what we do, see our offer, maybe it is you we will have the pleasure to meet :)

We are looking for a Data Engineer to join our team in mission to provide our customers with world-class applications that are used to discover and read magazines.

Project is a digital subscription service that lets customers have unlimited, “all-you-can-read” access to thousands of national and international magazines – all in one app.
As Data Engineer, you will... mostly work on the development of new features: now our team is creating recommendation system for users and Data Engineers are adding automatization in AWS. This means that based on the publications read and viewed, suggestions similar to the users' preferences will be displayed. Main aim is to ensure backend stack is an enabler for the future, so as to best manage the underlying business logic and integrations, such as content preparation, APIs, CRM tool integration, data warehouse integrations, etc. You will work in collaboration with your team in shaping the direction of our complete stack portfolio and the corresponding development processes. Our stack in the backend consists of Ruby, MongoDB, AWS, Golang, Redshift, RabbitMQ, Linux, and Docker.

You might be the perfect match if you:
• worked in the role of Data Engineer for at least 3 years ;
• have at least 3 years of experience in Python;
• care about quality and you know what it means to ship high-quality code;
• need to have the passion and curiosity to seek and find solutions on your own, but the experience and lack of prestige to be able to know when to rather go to a colleague for input and help;
• have preferably experience in AWS, Mongo DB, Snowflake, Redshift, and Elastic Search (it is nice to have ).

From the Data Engineer's point of view, the biggest advantages of working in this project are:
• a lot of independence - just take a ticket using your ideas and knowledge;
• an openness to the exchange of knowledge and discussion of current problems;
• opportunity to learn Go and Terraform from scratch;
• being part of all decision-making meetings and having an impact on what will be done and how.

By joining us, you gain the following:
• Exciting projects , multinational and inspiring environment for talented IT professionals. Various projects in diverse, cutting-edge industries: Biotech, Automotive, Internet of Things, or AR/VR;
• Code review done by skilled engineers (over 60% of our team are people with over 5 years of experience in the industry);
• Becoming a part of a team of motivated individuals, that are here to stay. We value loyalty – as you grow, we grow with you;
• Respect for your private life so you don't have to work overtime or on weekends;
• Online and offline integration events - including remote X-mass party and annual WOW tour trip abroad - so far we've been in Cape Town and Barcelona.

Perks and benefits:
• Fully remote work from your convenience or in our office in Wrocław or Warsaw;
• Choice of employment form: we offer B2B or employment contract;
• Free benefits such as Luxmed , Multisport , and life insurance in Nationale Nederlanden;
• Attractive referral system (8k for senior, 5k for mid, 2k for junior);
• Personal Training Budged and Passion Day - an extra day off for - your passion, hobby, and growth to spend as you please;
• Flexible working hours with no micromanagement approach. Our core hours are 9-15, the rest of the working time is your decision;
• We provide high-quality work equipment + 2 additional monitors and accessories.

If you apply for this position and match our expectations, then:

1) You will be invited to talk with Magda – IT Recruiter.

2) You will have a short meeting with our client.

